0443.Description: Its original home is an area much hotter than Alola. If you're planning to live with one, your heating bill will soar.

0444.Name: gabite
0444.Description: It sheds its skin and gradually grows larger. Its scales can be ground into a powder and used as raw materials for traditional medicine.

0445.Name: garchomp
0445.Description: Its fine scales don't just reduce wind resistance—their sharp edges also cause injury to any opponent who attacks it.

0446.Name: munchlax
0446.Description: Anything that looks edible, Munchlax will go on and swallow whole. Its stomach is tough enough to handle it even if the food has gone rotten.

0447.Name: riolu
0447.Description: It uses waves called auras to communicate with others of its kind. It doesn't make any noise during this time, so its enemies can't detect it.

0448.Name: lucario
0448.Description: Lucario reads its opponent's feelings with its aura waves. It finds out things it would rather not know, so it gets stressed out easily.

0449.Name: hippopotas
0449.Description: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.

0450.Name: hippowdon
0450.Description: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.

0451.Name: skorupi
0451.Description: It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey. Its tail claws can inject its prey with a savage poison.

0452.Name: drapion
0452.Description: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.

0453.Name: croagunk
0453.Description: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

0454.Name: toxicroak
0454.Description: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

0455.Name: carnivine
0455.Description: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

0456.Name: finneon
0456.Description: It lures in prey with its shining tail fins. It stays near the surface during the day and moves to the depths when night falls.

0457.Name: lumineon
0457.Description: They traverse the deep waters as if crawling over the seafloor. The fantastic lights of its fins shine like stars in the night sky.

0458.Name: mantyke
0458.Description: Mantyke are friendly toward people and will approach boats closely. The patterns on their backs differ depending on their habitat.

0459.Name: snover
0459.Description: In the spring, it grows berries with the texture of frozen treats around its belly.

0460.Name: abomasnow
0460.Description: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

0461.Name: weavile
0461.Description: Thanks to its increased intelligence, scrapping over food is a thing of the past. A scratch from its claws will give you a case of frostbite!

0462.Name: magnezone
0462.Description: There are still people who believe that this Pokémon came from outer space. It emanates a powerful magnetic field.

0463.Name: lickilicky
0463.Description: It uses its tongue much more skillfully than its hands or its feet. It can deftly pick up a single small bean with its tongue.

0464.Name: rhyperior
0464.Description: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. Geodude are shot at rare times.

0465.Name: tangrowth
0465.Description: Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm season, you can't even see its eyes.

0466.Name: electivire
0466.Description: A single Electivire can provide enough electricity for all the buildings in a big city for a year.

0467.Name: magmortar
0467.Description: Magmortar takes down its enemies by shooting fireballs, which burn them to a blackened crisp. It avoids this method when hunting prey.

0468.Name: togekiss
0468.Description: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.

0469.Name: yanmega
0469.Description: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

0470.Name: leafeon
0470.Description: It gets its nutrition from photosynthesis. It lives a quiet life deep in forests where clean rivers flow.

0471.Name: glaceon
0471.Description: It can instantaneously freeze any moisture that's around it, creating ice pellets to shoot at its prey.

0472.Name: gliscor
0472.Description: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

0473.Name: mamoswine
0473.Description: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

0474.Name: porygon-z
0474.Description: A faulty update was added to its programming. Its behavior is noticeably strange, so the experiment may have been a failure.

0475.Name: gallade
0475.Description: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

0476.Name: probopass
0476.Description: It uses three small units to catch prey and battle enemies. The main body mostly just gives orders.

0477.Name: dusknoir
0477.Description: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

0478.Name: froslass
0478.Description: It's said that on nights of terrible blizzards, it comes down to human settlements. If you hear it knocking at your door, do not open it!

0479.Name: rotom
0479.Description: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

0480.Name: uxie
0480.Description: It is said that its emergence gave humans the intelligence to improve their quality of life.

0481.Name: mesprit
0481.Description: It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake's surface.

0482.Name: azelf
0482.Description: It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came from the same egg.

0483.Name: dialga
0483.Description: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

0484.Name: palkia
0484.Description: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

0485.Name: heatran
0485.Description: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.

0486.Name: regigigas
0486.Description: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

0487.Name: giratina-altered
0487.Description: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.

0488.Name: cresselia
0488.Description: Those who sleep holding Cresselia's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

0489.Name: phione
0489.Description: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

0490.Name: manaphy
0490.Description: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

0491.Name: darkrai
0491.Description: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

0492.Name: shaymin-land
0492.Description: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.

0493.Name: arceus
0493.Description: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.

0494.Name: victini
0494.Description: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.

0495.Name: snivy
0495.Description: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

0496.Name: servine
0496.Description: When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.

0497.Name: serperior
0497.Description: It can stop its opponents' movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

0498.Name: tepig
0498.Description: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

0499.Name: pignite
0499.Description: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

0500.Name: emboar
0500.Description: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.

0501.Name: oshawott
0501.Description: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

0502.Name: dewott
0502.Description: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.

0503.Name: samurott
0503.Description: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

0504.Name: patrat
0504.Description: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won't notice a foe coming from behind.

0505.Name: watchog
0505.Description: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

0506.Name: lillipup
0506.Description: This Pokémon is popular with beginners because it's intelligent, obedient to its Trainer's commands, and easy to raise.

0507.Name: herdier
0507.Description: It has been living with people for so long that portrayals of it can be found on the walls of caves from long, long ago.

0508.Name: stoutland
0508.Description: Its fur is long and thick. A long time ago in cold regions, every household kept a Stoutland.

0509.Name: purrloin
0509.Description: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can't help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

0510.Name: liepard
0510.Description: Stealthily, it sneaks up on its target, striking from behind before its victim has a chance to react.

0511.Name: pansage
0511.Description: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

0512.Name: simisage
0512.Description: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

0513.Name: pansear
0513.Description: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

0514.Name: simisear
0514.Description: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.

0515.Name: panpour
0515.Description: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

0516.Name: simipour
0516.Description: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

0517.Name: munna
0517.Description: It eats the dreams of people and Pokémon. When it eats a pleasant dream, it expels pink-colored mist.

0518.Name: musharna
0518.Description: The dream mist coming from its forehead changes into many different colors depending on the dream that was eaten.

0519.Name: pidove
0519.Description: These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.

0520.Name: tranquill
0520.Description: No matter where in the world it goes, it knows where its nest is, so it never gets separated from its Trainer.

0521.Name: unfezant
0521.Description: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.

0522.Name: blitzle
0522.Description: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

0523.Name: zebstrika
0523.Description: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

0524.Name: roggenrola
0524.Description: It was found in a fissure in a layer of exposed rock. The material that makes up its body is dirt from several hundred years ago.

0525.Name: boldore
0525.Description: Its orange crystals are lumps of powerful energy. They're valuable, so Boldore is sometimes targeted for them.

0526.Name: gigalith
0526.Description: It absorbs rays of sunlight and shoots out energy. It's usually lurking deep beneath the surface.

0527.Name: woobat
0527.Description: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.

0528.Name: swoobat
0528.Description: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.

0529.Name: drilbur
0529.Description: By spinning its body, it can dig straight through the ground at a speed of 30 mph.

0530.Name: excadrill
0530.Description: More than 300 feet below the surface, they build mazelike nests. Their activity can be destructive to subway tunnels.

0531.Name: audino
0531.Description: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

0532.Name: timburr
0532.Description: Always carrying squared logs, they help out with construction. As they grow, they carry bigger logs.

0533.Name: gurdurr
0533.Description: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

0534.Name: conkeldurr
0534.Description: Rather than rely on force, they master moves that utilize the centrifugal force of spinning concrete.

0535.Name: tympole
0535.Description: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

0536.Name: palpitoad
0536.Description: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to immobilize its opponents.

0537.Name: seismitoad
0537.Description: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

0538.Name: throh
0538.Description: When it encounters a foe bigger than itself, it wants to throw it. It changes belts as it gets stronger.

0539.Name: sawk
0539.Description: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.

0540.Name: sewaddle
0540.Description: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

0541.Name: swadloon
0541.Description: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.

0542.Name: leavanny
0542.Description: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

0543.Name: venipede
0543.Description: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

0544.Name: whirlipede
0544.Description: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.

0545.Name: scolipede
0545.Description: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

0546.Name: cottonee
0546.Description: When attacked, it expels cotton from its body to create a diversion. The cotton it loses grows back in quickly.

0547.Name: whimsicott
0547.Description: Whimsicott doesn't live in a fixed location. It floats around on whirling winds, appearing all over the place to perform its mischief.

0548.Name: petilil
0548.Description: They prefer clean water and soil. When the environment they live in turns bad, the whole bunch will up and move to a new area.

0549.Name: lilligant
0549.Description: It's well liked by other Pokémon because of its beauty. The flower on its head needs constant care, or it will soon wither and rot.

0550.Name: basculin-red-striped
0550.Description: When a school of Basculin appears in a lake, everything else disappears, except for Corphish and Crawdaunt. That's how violent Basculin are.

0551.Name: sandile
0551.Description: Sandile's still not good at hunting, so it mostly eats things that have collapsed in the desert. It's called "the cleaner of the desert."201d

0552.Name: krokorok
0552.Description: It buries some of its prey in the sand to use as emergency meals when its hunts are unsuccessful.

0553.Name: krookodile
0553.Description: It conceals itself in sandstorms that Flygon whip up and waits patiently for prey to appear.

0554.Name: darumaka
0554.Description: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.

0555.Name: darmanitan-standard
0555.Description: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

0556.Name: maractus
0556.Description: Arid regions are their habitat. They move rhythmically, making a sound similar to maracas.

0557.Name: dwebble
0557.Description: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.

0558.Name: crustle
0558.Description: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

0559.Name: scraggy
0559.Description: It stretches its saggy skin up to its neck to protect itself. The saggier their skin, the more respect they garner.

0560.Name: scrafty
0560.Description: It taunts its opponents by spitting. It has a certain territory that it never leaves its whole life long.

0561.Name: sigilyph
0561.Description: The guardians of an ancient city, they always fly the same route while keeping watch for invaders.

0562.Name: yamask
0562.Description: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

0563.Name: cofagrigus
0563.Description: Grave robbers who mistake them for real coffins and get too close end up trapped inside their bodies.

0564.Name: tirtouga
0564.Description: Its hunting grounds encompassed a broad area, from the land to more than half a mile deep in the ocean.

0565.Name: carracosta
0565.Description: Carracosta eats every last bit of the prey it catches, even the shells and bones, to further strengthen its sturdy shell.

0566.Name: archen
0566.Description: Restored from a fossil, this ancient bird Pokémon has wings but can't yet fly.

0567.Name: archeops
0567.Description: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, the muscles it uses to flap its wings are still weak, so it needs a long runway in order to take off.

0568.Name: trubbish
0568.Description: If a young Pokémon or child breathes in the toxic gas that Trubbish belches out, it could be a life-threatening situation.

0569.Name: garbodor
0569.Description: Some say the reason Garbodor in Alola are a little stronger than their counterparts elsewhere is the presence of Muk, their natural enemy.

0570.Name: zorua
0570.Description: If a normally talkative child suddenly stops talking, it may have been replaced by Zorua.

0571.Name: zoroark
0571.Description: If it thinks humans are going to discover its den, Zoroark shows them visions that make them wander around in the woods.

0572.Name: minccino
0572.Description: When its tail has gotten dirty from self-cleaning or from cleaning its nest, Minccino spends a whole day washing its tail in clean spring water.

0573.Name: cinccino
0573.Description: The oil that seeps from its body is really smooth. For people troubled by bad skin, this oil is an effective treatment.

0574.Name: gothita
0574.Description: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.

0575.Name: gothorita
0575.Description: According to many old tales, it creates friends for itself by controlling sleeping children on starry nights.

0576.Name: gothitelle
0576.Description: They can predict the future from the placement and movement of the stars. They can see Trainers' life spans.

0577.Name: solosis
0577.Description: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

0578.Name: duosion
0578.Description: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.

0579.Name: reuniclus
0579.Description: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

0580.Name: ducklett
0580.Description: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

0581.Name: swanna
0581.Description: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

0582.Name: vanillite
0582.Description: When the morning sun hit an icicle, it wished not to melt, and thus Vanillite was born. At night, it buries itself in snow to sleep.

0583.Name: vanillish
0583.Description: This hearty Pokémon survived the Ice Age. It's incredibly popular in very hot regions.

0584.Name: vanilluxe
0584.Description: Vanilluxe is born when two Vanillish, half-melted by the day's light, stick to each other and freeze together in the cold return of night.

0585.Name: deerling
0585.Description: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

0586.Name: sawsbuck
0586.Description: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.

0587.Name: emolga
0587.Description: As it flies, it scatters electricity around, so bird Pokémon keep their distance. That's why Emolga can keep all its food to itself.

0588.Name: karrablast
0588.Description: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.

0589.Name: escavalier
0589.Description: These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.

0590.Name: foongus
0590.Description: It lures Pokémon with its pattern that looks just like a Poké Ball, then releases poison spores.

0591.Name: amoonguss
0591.Description: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

0592.Name: frillish
0592.Description: Using the invisible poison spikes on its veillike arms and legs, it paralyzes its enemies and causes them to drown.

0593.Name: jellicent
0593.Description: Fishermen are terrified of Jellicent. It's rumored to drag them into the sea and steal their lives away.

0594.Name: alomomola
0594.Description: The reason it helps Pokémon in a weakened condition is that any Pokémon coming after them may also attack Alomomola.

0595.Name: joltik
0595.Description: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.

0596.Name: galvantula
0596.Description: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

0597.Name: ferroseed
0597.Description: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.

0598.Name: ferrothorn
0598.Description: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.

0599.Name: klink
0599.Description: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

0600.Name: klang
0600.Description: A minigear and big gear comprise its body. If the minigear it launches at a foe doesn't return, it will die.

0601.Name: klinklang
0601.Description: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.

0602.Name: tynamo
0602.Description: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

0603.Name: eelektrik
0603.Description: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

0604.Name: eelektross
0604.Description: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

0605.Name: elgyem
0605.Description: This Pokémon is shrouded in mystery. It's said to have appeared from a UFO that fell from the sky about 50 years ago.

0606.Name: beheeyem
0606.Description: It has strong psychic powers. Using its fingers that flash three different colors, it controls its opponents and rewrites their memories.

0607.Name: litwick
0607.Description: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

0608.Name: lampent
0608.Description: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.

0609.Name: chandelure
0609.Description: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.

0610.Name: axew
0610.Description: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.

0611.Name: fraxure
0611.Description: A broken tusk will not grow back, so it diligently sharpens its tusks on river rocks after the end of a battle.

0612.Name: haxorus
0612.Description: Their sturdy tusks will stay sharp even if used to cut steel beams. These Pokémon are covered in hard armor.

0613.Name: cubchoo
0613.Description: Their snot is a barometer of health. When healthy, their snot is sticky and the power of their ice moves increases.

0614.Name: beartic
0614.Description: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.

0615.Name: cryogonal
0615.Description: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148 degrees Fahrenheit.

0616.Name: shelmet
0616.Description: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.

0617.Name: accelgor
0617.Description: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

0618.Name: stunfisk
0618.Description: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.

0619.Name: mienfoo
0619.Description: They seclude themselves in the mountains and devote themselves to training. The form of their kicks and chops differs from pack to pack.

0620.Name: mienshao
0620.Description: When Mienshao lets out a bizarre wail, you're in danger. A flurry of kicks and chops too fast to see is about to be unleashed!

0621.Name: druddigon
0621.Description: It infiltrates tunnels that Pokémon like Diglett and Dugtrio have dug and quietly waits for prey to pass through.

0622.Name: golett
0622.Description: Although ancient people apparently built it by working with clay, the source of its energy is unclear.

0623.Name: golurk
0623.Description: When the seal on its chest is removed, it rages indiscriminately, turning the whole town around it into a mountain of rubble.

0624.Name: pawniard
0624.Description: It follows Bisharp's orders to a tee when it attacks enemies. After slashing an opponent, Pawniard clangs both of its blades together.

0625.Name: bisharp
0625.Description: It leads a group of Pawniard. Bisharp doesn't even change its expression when it deals the finishing blow to an opponent.

0626.Name: bouffalant
0626.Description: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

0627.Name: rufflet
0627.Description: Known as a natural-born warrior, soon after its hatching, it will challenge its parent to a fight in order to gain their acceptance.

0628.Name: braviary
0628.Description: Known as "the hero of the skies,"201d this Pokémon is so proud and so brave that it will never retreat, even when it's injured.

0629.Name: vullaby
0629.Description: Its healthy appetite leads to visible growth spurts. It often has to replace the bones it wears as its size increases.

0630.Name: mandibuzz
0630.Description: It's always searching for food for Vullaby. When it finds a weak Pokémon, Mandibuzz swoops it right off to its nest.

0631.Name: heatmor
0631.Description: It draws in air through its tail, transforms it into fire, and uses it like a tongue. It melts Durant and eats them.

0632.Name: durant
0632.Description: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

0633.Name: deino
0633.Description: Lacking sight, it's unaware of its surroundings, so it bumps into things and eats anything that moves.

0634.Name: zweilous
0634.Description: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

0635.Name: hydreigon
0635.Description: It responds to movement by attacking. This scary, three-headed Pokémon devours everything in its path!

0636.Name: larvesta
0636.Description: It protects itself with flame. Long years ago, people believed Larvesta had a nest on the sun.

0637.Name: volcarona
0637.Description: According to legends, it was hatched from a flaming cocoon to save people and Pokémon that were suffering from the cold.

0638.Name: cobalion
0638.Description: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokémon.

0639.Name: terrakion
0639.Description: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.

0640.Name: virizion
0640.Description: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.

0641.Name: tornadus-incarnate
0641.Description: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

0642.Name: thundurus-incarnate
0642.Description: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.

0643.Name: reshiram
0643.Description: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.

0644.Name: zekrom
0644.Description: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

0645.Name: landorus-incarnate
0645.Description: From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.

0646.Name: kyurem
0646.Description: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

0647.Name: keldeo-ordinary
0647.Description: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

0648.Name: meloetta-aria
0648.Description: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

0649.Name: genesect
0649.Description: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

0650.Name: chespin
0650.Description: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and back that even a direct hit from a truck wouldn't faze it.

0651.Name: quilladin
0651.Description: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won't start fights.

0652.Name: chesnaught
0652.Description: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.

0653.Name: fennekin
0653.Description: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.

0654.Name: braixen
0654.Description: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.

0655.Name: delphox
0655.Description: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.

0656.Name: froakie
0656.Description: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

0657.Name: frogadier
0657.Description: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute's time.

0658.Name: greninja
0658.Description: It appears and vanishes with a ninja's grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

0659.Name: bunnelby
0659.Description: It has ears like shovels. Digging holes strengthens its ears so much that they can sever thick roots effortlessly.

0660.Name: diggersby
0660.Description: As powerful as an excavator, its ears can reduce dense bedrock to rubble. When it's finished digging, it lounges lazily.

0661.Name: fletchling
0661.Description: Its body is always warm. Trainers who live in cold areas apparently sleep with it in their bed.

0662.Name: fletchinder
0662.Description: Its speed right after takeoff already puts it in the top speed class of all bird Pokémon.

0663.Name: talonflame
0663.Description: Bird Pokémon make up most of its diet. It approaches at high speeds and smacks them down to the ground with its powerful kick.

0664.Name: scatterbug
0664.Description: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.

0665.Name: spewpa
0665.Description: The beaks of bird Pokémon can't begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.

0666.Name: vivillon
0666.Description: The patterns on this Pokémon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

0667.Name: litleo
0667.Description: This hot-blooded Pokémon is filled with curiosity. When it gets angry or starts fighting, its short mane gets hot.

0668.Name: pyroar
0668.Description: The temperature of its breath is over 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, but Pyroar doesn't use it on its prey. This Pokémon prefers to eat raw meat.

0669.Name: flabebe
0669.Description: Flabébé wears a crown made from pollen it's collected from its flower. The crown has hidden healing properties.

0670.Name: floette
0670.Description: It gives its own power to flowers, pouring its heart into caring for them. Floette never forgives anyone who messes up a flower bed.

0671.Name: florges
0671.Description: Its life can span several hundred years. It's said to devote its entire life to protecting gardens.

0672.Name: skiddo
0672.Description: If it has sunshine and water, it doesn't need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.

0673.Name: gogoat
0673.Description: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.

0674.Name: pancham
0674.Description: It's desperate to intimidate its opponents. Be nice and pretend to be scared if you catch it glaring at you intensely.

0675.Name: pangoro
0675.Description: Pangoro is the type to talk with its fists. It doesn't say much as it pummels opponents with enough force to send a dump truck flying.

0676.Name: furfrou
0676.Description: Left alone, its fur will grow longer and longer, but it will only allow someone it trusts to cut it.

0677.Name: espurr
0677.Description: It has enough psychic energy to blast everything within 300 feet of itself, but it has no control over its power.

0678.Name: meowstic-male
0678.Description: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.

0679.Name: honedge
0679.Description: If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person's arm and drains that person's life energy completely.

0680.Name: doublade
0680.Description: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.

0681.Name: aegislash-shield
0681.Description: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.

0682.Name: spritzee
0682.Description: In the past, rather than using perfume, royal ladies carried a Spritzee that would waft a fragrance they liked.

0683.Name: aromatisse
0683.Description: Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy the smell, he or she will have a hard time walking alongside it.

0684.Name: swirlix
0684.Description: Because it eats nothing but sweets, its fur is as sticky sweet as cotton candy.

0685.Name: slurpuff
0685.Description: Its sense of smell is 100 million times better than a human's, so even the faintest scent tells it about everything in the area. It's like it can see with its nose!

0686.Name: inkay
0686.Description: When exchanging information with others of its kind, it flashes the light-emitting spots on its body in a complex rhythm.

0687.Name: malamar
0687.Description: It flashes the pattern on its torso to control its prey and draw them in. The edges of its fins are supremely sharp.

0688.Name: binacle
0688.Description: They stretch and then contract, yanking their rocks along with them in bold hops. They eat seaweed that washes up on the shoreline.

0689.Name: barbaracle
0689.Description: Barbaracle's legs and hands have minds of their own, and they will move independently. But they usually follow the head's orders.

0690.Name: skrelp
0690.Description: It's not good at swimming, so it clings to the seaweed. In the Alola region, it's often found near Dhelmise.

0691.Name: dragalge
0691.Description: It blends in with seaweed to ambush its prey and then takes them down with a poisonous liquid strong enough to melt metal.

0692.Name: clauncher
0692.Description: It moves around by jetting water from its right pincer. It has a poor sense of balance, so it's terrible at swimming straight.

0693.Name: clawitzer
0693.Description: Its right arm is packed with meat. When its pincer falls off, it's exported to be used as a cooking ingredient.

0694.Name: helioptile
0694.Description: The frills on either side of its head have cells that generate electricity when exposed to sunlight.

0695.Name: heliolisk
0695.Description: It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.

0696.Name: tyrunt
0696.Description: Tyrunt is spoiled and selfish. It may just be trying to frolic, but sometimes the ones it's trying to frolic with are gravely injured.

0697.Name: tyrantrum
0697.Description: The king of the ancient world, it can easily crunch a car with the devastating strength of its enormous jaws.

0698.Name: amaura
0698.Description: Amaura was restored successfully, but it's not expected to live long because of the heat of the current environment.

0699.Name: aurorus
0699.Description: This usually quiet and kindly Pokémon has a surface temperature of around "2013240 degrees Fahrenheit.

0700.Name: sylveon
0700.Description: Sylveon wraps its ribbonlike feelers around its Trainer's arm because this touch enables it to read its Trainer's feelings.

0701.Name: hawlucha
0701.Description: In combat, Hawlucha leaps nimbly about, taking advantage of its opponents' blind spots. It's also skilled at using superb submission holds.

0702.Name: dedenne
0702.Description: Its upper whiskers are sensors that survey its surroundings. Its lower whiskers are organs that shoot electricity.

0703.Name: carbink
0703.Description: To keep the jewels on their bodies free of tarnish, packs of Carbink use their soft manes to polish one another's jewels.

0704.Name: goomy
0704.Description: Its body is mostly water. If it dries out, it will die, so it's always sitting with perfect stillness in the shade.

0705.Name: sliggoo
0705.Description: Its entire body is covered with gooey mucus that can dissolve anything. Be sure to put gloves on if you're going to touch it.

0706.Name: goodra
0706.Description: Underneath its slimy skin is a thick layer of fat, and the combination of the two makes enemies' attacks slide right off.

0707.Name: klefki
0707.Description: Long ago it lived in mines, but once the minerals that make up its diet became scarcer, Klefki began appearing in human settlements.

0708.Name: phantump
0708.Description: An unknown spirit came to lodge in a tree stump, creating this Pokémon. A cure-all can be made from an infusion of its green leaves.

0709.Name: trevenant
0709.Description: This Pokémon controls trees via roots stretching from its feet, and it will attack anyone that dares to ravage the forest.

0710.Name: pumpkaboo-average
0710.Description: It is said to carry wandering spirits to the place where they belong so they can move on.

0711.Name: gourgeist-average
0711.Description: It enwraps its prey in its hairlike arms. It sings joyfully as it observes the suffering of its prey.

0712.Name: bergmite
0712.Description: Using air of -150 degrees Fahrenheit, they freeze opponents solid. They live in herds above the snow line on mountains.

0713.Name: avalugg
0713.Description: The way several Bergmite huddle on its back makes it look like an aircraft carrier made of ice.

0714.Name: noibat
0714.Description: It flies around in search of fruit to eat. It uses ultrasonic waves to detect which fruits are ripe.

0715.Name: noivern
0715.Description: This hot-blooded Pokémon attacks anything it sees with ultrasonic waves that can crush boulders.

0716.Name: xerneas
0716.Description: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.

0717.Name: yveltal
0717.Description: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

0718.Name: zygarde
0718.Description: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

0719.Name: diancie
0719.Description: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.

0720.Name: hoopa
0720.Description: It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.

0721.Name: volcanion
0721.Description: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

0722.Name: rowlet
0722.Description: It feels relaxed in tight, dark places and has been known to use its Trainer's pocket or bag as a nest.

0723.Name: dartrix
0723.Description: Supremely sensitive to the presence of others, it can detect opponents standing behind it, flinging its sharp feathers to take them out.

0724.Name: decidueye
0724.Description: Decidueye can nock and fire an arrow at an enemy in a tenth of a second, so its battles are decided in the blink of an eye.

0725.Name: litten
0725.Description: Its coat regrows twice a year. When the time comes, Litten sets its own body on fire and burns away the old fur.

0726.Name: torracat
0726.Description: When its mane is standing on end, you can tell it's feeling good. When it isn't feeling well, its fur will lie down flat.

0727.Name: incineroar
0727.Description: When its fighting spirit is set alight, the flames around its waist become especially intense.

0728.Name: popplio
0728.Description: Popplio gets on top of its bouncy water balloons to jump higher. It's quite the acrobatic fighter!

0729.Name: brionne
0729.Description: It attacks by smacking its enemies with the exploding water balloons that it creates.

0730.Name: primarina
0730.Description: Also known as a songstress, it has a fantastical look on moonlit nights when it leads its colony in song.

0731.Name: pikipek
0731.Description: It may look spindly, but its neck muscles are heavy-duty. It can peck at a tree 16 times per second!

0732.Name: trumbeak
0732.Description: From its mouth, it fires the seeds of berries it has eaten. The scattered seeds give rise to new plants.

0733.Name: toucannon
0733.Description: Known for forming harmonious couples, this Pokémon is brought to wedding ceremonies as a good luck charm.

0734.Name: yungoos
0734.Description: Although it will eat anything, it prefers fresh living things, so it marches down streets in search of prey.

0735.Name: gumshoos
0735.Description: Patient by nature, this Pokémon loses control of itself and pounces when it spots its favorite meal—Rattata!

0736.Name: grubbin
0736.Description: It spits a sticky thread to stop opponents in their tracks, and then it grabs them in its sharp, sturdy mandibles to take them down.

0737.Name: charjabug
0737.Description: Its stout shell provides excellent defense from attacks. It uses electricity on persistent opponents.

0738.Name: vikavolt
0738.Description: Vikavolt flusters opponents with acrobatic flying maneuvers. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electric beam attack.

0739.Name: crabrawler
0739.Description: Crabrawler has been known to mistake Exeggutor for a coconut tree and climb it. The enraged Exeggutor shakes it off and stomps it.

0740.Name: crabominable
0740.Description: Before it stops to think, it just starts pummeling. There are records of its turning back avalanches with a flurry of punches.

0741.Name: oricorio-baile
0741.Description: This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokémon becomes fiercely angry.

0742.Name: cutiefly
0742.Description: Cutiefly can pick up the auras of living things. It skillfully reads those auras to predict its foes' movements and make fools of them.

0743.Name: ribombee
0743.Description: It can predict the weather from moisture levels and wind direction. Ribombee only reveals itself when there are a few clear days in a row.

0744.Name: rockruff
0744.Description: When it rubs the rocks on its neck against you, that's proof of its love for you. However, the rocks are sharp, so the gesture is quite painful!

0745.Name: lycanroc-midday
0745.Description: The rocks in its mane are sharper than a knife. Fragments that break off are treasured as good luck charms.

0746.Name: wishiwashi-solo
0746.Description: When it's in a jam, its shining eyes attract others of its kind. The light from its eyes is visible almost 25 miles away.

0747.Name: mareanie
0747.Description: Aside from its head, its body parts regenerate quickly if they're cut off. After a good night's sleep, Mareanie is back to normal.

0748.Name: toxapex
0748.Description: With its 12 legs, it creates a dome to shelter within. The flow of the tides doesn't affect Toxapex in there, so it's very comfortable.

0749.Name: mudbray
0749.Description: Possessing mighty power, Mudbray can be loaded with 50 times its own body weight and will be totally fine.

0750.Name: mudsdale
0750.Description: It can trudge mountain roads without rest for three days and three nights, all the while dragging a 10-ton load.

0751.Name: dewpider
0751.Description: It can only breathe oxygen that has dissolved in water, so it wears a water bubble on its head when it walks around on land.

0752.Name: araquanid
0752.Description: It has a habit of storing things it values in its water bubble. If its Trainer doesn't watch out, Araquanid will try to put them in its bubble!

0753.Name: fomantis
0753.Description: It loves the sunshine. When it basks in the sunlight regularly, it grows up with vivid coloration.

0754.Name: lurantis
0754.Description: As it slashes into its enemies, it looks like it's dancing. Its elegant appearance has led some to call it the most glamorous Grass Pokémon.

0755.Name: morelull
0755.Description: It likes damp dark places. When night falls, the spores filling the caps of its mushrooms glow.

0756.Name: shiinotic
0756.Description: When it starts fighting for territory with Parasect, the entire area gets completely coated in spores!

0757.Name: salandit
0757.Description: It weakens opponents and sends them reeling with its poisonous gas. Salandit doesn't deal well with Spinda, since it's always reeling.

0758.Name: salazzle
0758.Description: It punishes Salandit that couldn't bring it food with a fierce slap of its flame-spewing palm.

0759.Name: stufful
0759.Description: Stufful hates to be hugged or touched in any way. It will squirm, thrash, and resist with amazing power.

0760.Name: bewear
0760.Description: It boasts tremendous physical strength. Many people call it the most dangerous Pokémon in the Alola region.

0761.Name: bounsweet
0761.Description: It tries to resist being swallowed by a bird Pokémon by spinning the sepals on its head. It's usually a fruitless attempt.

0762.Name: steenee
0762.Description: It bounces around, swinging the sepals on its head with abandon. They're quite painful when they smack you!

0763.Name: tsareena
0763.Description: A Pokémon with an aggressive personality and a mastery of kicking, it cackles every time it kicks an opponent.

0764.Name: comfey
0764.Description: It picks flowers and sticks them to its body with fluids it produces. The aroma that wafts from its petals has a healing effect.

0765.Name: oranguru
0765.Description: Oranguru don't get along with each other, so they're always engaging in battles of wits to decide which one is superior.

0766.Name: passimian
0766.Description: Berries are its weapons as well as the staple of its diet. The one that can throw a berry the farthest is the boss of the troop.

0767.Name: wimpod
0767.Description: An astonishingly cowardly Pokémon, Wimpod will whir its legs at high speeds to run away if anything comes near it.

0768.Name: golisopod
0768.Description: Its claws, which it can extend and retract at will, are its greatest weapons. Golisopod is sometimes accompanied by Wimpod.

0769.Name: sandygast
0769.Description: If you build sand mounds when you're playing, destroy them before you go home, or they may get possessed and become Sandygast.

0770.Name: palossand
0770.Description: Once it has whipped up a sandstorm to halt its opponents in their tracks, this terrifying Pokémon snatches away their vitality.

0771.Name: pyukumuku
0771.Description: Its entire body is covered in its own slime. If you accidentally step on one, you'll slip, and it will get mad and smack you!

0772.Name: type-null
0772.Description: There's danger of its going on a rampage, so its true power is sealed away beneath its control mask.

0773.Name: silvally
0773.Description: Through the bond it formed with its Trainer, its will was strengthened, and it was able to destroy its control mask.

0774.Name: minior-red-meteor
0774.Description: Although its outer shell is uncommonly durable, the shock of falling to the ground smashes the shell to smithereens.

0775.Name: komala
0775.Description: It remains asleep from birth to death as a result of the sedative properties of the leaves that form its diet.

0776.Name: turtonator
0776.Description: Its exploding shell poses a real danger but is sensitive to moisture. On rainy days, Turtonator takes silent refuge in caves.

0777.Name: togedemaru
0777.Description: Its capacity to produce electricity is somewhat limited, so it gets charged up by letting lightning strike it!

0778.Name: mimikyu-disguised
0778.Description: A gust of wind revealed what hides under this Pokémon's rag to a passing Trainer, who went home and died painfully that very night.

0779.Name: bruxish
0779.Description: Its skin is thick enough to fend off Mareanie's spikes. With its robust teeth, Bruxish crunches up the spikes and eats them.

0780.Name: drampa
0780.Description: It appears in towns and plays with the children. Drampa will protect kids when they're in danger, so their moms don't have to worry.

0781.Name: dhelmise
0781.Description: Its chain-like green seaweed can stretch outward for hundreds of yards. For some reason, it gets along well with Skrelp.

0782.Name: jangmo-o
0782.Description: It will never show an enemy its back in battle. Ancient warriors liked Jangmo-o for its valiant disposition and made it one of their own.

0783.Name: hakamo-o
0783.Description: The scales it sheds can be molded and processed to make pots and pans. They conduct heat well, so they're a popular item.

0784.Name: kommo-o
0784.Description: It battles valiantly with its fists, which are armored in steel scales. Kommo-o specializes in uppercuts.

0785.Name: tapu-koko
0785.Description: The lightning-wielding guardian deity of Melemele, Tapu Koko is brimming with curiosity and appears before people from time to time.

0786.Name: tapu-lele
0786.Description: Although called a guardian deity, Tapu Lele is devoid of guilt about its cruel disposition and can be described as nature incarnate.

0787.Name: tapu-bulu
0787.Description: It makes ringing sounds with its tail to let others know where it is, avoiding unneeded conflicts. This guardian deity of Ula'ula controls plants.

0788.Name: tapu-fini
0788.Description: Although it's called a guardian deity, terrible calamities sometimes befall those who recklessly approach Tapu Fini.

0789.Name: cosmog
0789.Description: Whether or not it's a Pokémon from this world is a mystery. When it's in a jam, it warps away to a safe place to hide.

0790.Name: cosmoem
0790.Description: As it absorbs light, Cosmoem continues to grow. Its golden shell is surprisingly solid.

0791.Name: solgaleo
0791.Description: In writings from the distant past, it's called by the name "the beast that devours the sun."201d

0792.Name: lunala
0792.Description: It sometimes summons unknown powers and life-forms here to this world from holes that lead to other worlds.

0793.Name: nihilego
0793.Description: It appeared in this world from an Ultra Wormhole. Nihilego appears to be a parasite that lives by feeding on people and Pokémon.

0794.Name: buzzwole
0794.Description: Buzzwole goes around showing off its abnormally swollen muscles. It is one kind of Ultra Beast.

0795.Name: pheromosa
0795.Description: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

0796.Name: xurkitree
0796.Description: They've been dubbed Ultra Beasts. Some of them stand unmoving, like trees, with their arms and legs stuck into the ground.

0797.Name: celesteela
0797.Description: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

0798.Name: kartana
0798.Description: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

0799.Name: guzzlord
0799.Description: An unknown life-form called a UB. It may be constantly hungry—it is certainly always devouring something.

0800.Name: necrozma
0800.Description: Light is the source of its energy. If it isn't devouring light, impurities build up in it and on it, and Necrozma darkens and stops moving.

0801.Name: magearna
0801.Description: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

0802.Name: marshadow
0802.Description: It sinks into the shadows of people and Pokémon, where it can understand their feelings and copy their capabilities.

0803.Name: poipole
0803.Description: An Ultra Beast that lives in a different world, it cackles wildly as it sprays its opponents with poison from the needles on its head.

0804.Name: naganadel
0804.Description: One kind of Ultra Beast, it fires a glowing, venomous liquid from its needles. This liquid is also immensely adhesive.

0805.Name: stakataka
0805.Description: When stone walls started moving and attacking, the brute's true identity was this mysterious life-form, which brings to mind an Ultra Beast.

0806.Name: blacephalon
0806.Description: A UB that appeared from an Ultra Wormhole, it causes explosions, then takes advantage of opponents' surprise to rob them of their vitality.

0807.Name: zeraora
0807.Description: It approaches its enemies at the speed of lightning, then tears them limb from limb with its sharp claws.

0808.Name: Meltan
0808.Description: They live as a group, but when the time comes, one strong Meltan will absorb all the others and evolve.

0809.Name: Melmetal
0809.Description: Centrifugal force is behind the punches of Melmetal's heavy hex-nut arms. Melmetal is said to deliver the strongest punches of all Pokémon.

0810.Name: grookey
0810.Description: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area. It attacks with rapid beats of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more pumped.

0811.Name: thwackey
0811.Description: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers. When it's drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won't even notice that it's already knocked out its opponent.

0812.Name: rillaboom
0812.Description: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle. Gigantamax energy has caused Rillaboom's stump to grow into a drum set that resembles a forest. Rillaboom has become one with its forest of drums and continues to lay down beats that shake all of Galar. The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.

0813.Name: scorbunny
0813.Description: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon's body. Once that happens, it's ready to fight at full power. It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it's raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.

0814.Name: raboot
0814.Description: Its thick and fluffy fur protects it from the cold and enables it to use hotter fire moves. It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.

0815.Name: cinderace
0815.Description: Infused with Cinderace's fighting spirit, the gigantic Pyro Ball never misses its targets and completely roasts opponents. It juggles a pebble with its feet, turning it into a burning soccer ball. Its shots strike opponents hard and leave them scorched. Gigantamax energy can sometimes cause the diameter of this Pokémon's fireball to exceed 300 feet. It's skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.

0816.Name: sobble
0816.Description: When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won't be able to resist weeping. When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokémon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.

0817.Name: drizzile
0817.Description: A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms. Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.

0818.Name: inteleon
0818.Description: Gigantamax Inteleon's Water Gun move fires at Mach 7. As the Pokémon takes aim, it uses the crest on its head to gauge wind and temperature. It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air. It has excellent sniping skills. Shooting a berry rolling along over nine miles away is a piece of cake for this Pokémon. Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes' weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.

0819.Name: skwovet
0819.Description: Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries. It eats berries nonstop—a habit that has made it more resilient than it looks. It'll show up on farms, searching for yet more berries.

0820.Name: greedent
0820.Description: It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn't notice the loss. Common throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon has strong teeth and can chew through the toughest of berry shells.

0821.Name: rookidee
0821.Description: It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit. Jumping nimbly about, this small-bodied Pokémon takes advantage of even the slightest opportunity to disorient larger opponents.

0822.Name: corvisquire
0822.Description: Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies. The lessons of many harsh battles have taught it how to accurately judge an opponent's strength.

0823.Name: corviknight
0823.Description: Imbued with Gigantamax energy, its wings can whip up winds more forceful than any a hurricane could muster. The gusts blow everything away. This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe. The eight feathers on its back are called blade birds, and they can launch off its body to attack foes independently. With their great intellect and flying skills, these Pokémon very successfully act as the Galar region's airborne taxi service.

0824.Name: blipbug
0824.Description: A constant collector of information, this Pokémon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn't. Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

0825.Name: dottler
0825.Description: It barely moves, but it's still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers. As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

0826.Name: orbeetle
0826.Description: Its brain has grown to a gargantuan size, as has the rest of its body. This Pokémon's intellect and psychic abilities are overpowering. It's famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power. If it were to utilize every last bit of its power, it could control the minds of every living being in its vicinity. It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it—and what's around it can include things over six miles away.

0827.Name: nickit
0827.Description: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains. Cunning and cautious, this Pokémon survives by stealing food from others. It erases its tracks with swipes of its tail as it makes off with its plunder.

0828.Name: thievul
0828.Description: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it. With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. Boltund is its natural enemy.

0829.Name: gossifleur
0829.Description: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly. It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.

0830.Name: eldegoss
0830.Description: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them. The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.

0831.Name: wooloo
0831.Description: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed. If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won't be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.

0832.Name: dubwool
0832.Description: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You'll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it. Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.

0833.Name: chewtle
0833.Description: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it. It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokémon bites down and never lets go.

0834.Name: drednaw
0834.Description: It responded to Gigantamax energy by becoming bipedal. First it comes crashing down on foes, and then it finishes them off with its massive jaws. With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey. In the Galar region, there's a tale about this Pokémon chewing up a mountain and using the rubble to stop a flood. This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.

0835.Name: yamper
0835.Description: This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail. This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.

0836.Name: boltund
0836.Description: This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days. It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.

0837.Name: rolycoly
0837.Description: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago. It can race around like a unicycle, even on rough, rocky terrain. Burning coal sustains it.

0838.Name: carkol
0838.Description: It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by this Pokémon once helped fuel the lives of people in the Galar region. By rapidly rolling its legs, it can travel at over 18 mph. The temperature of the flames it breathes exceeds 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

0839.Name: coalossal
0839.Description: Its body is a colossal stove. With Gigantamax energy stoking the fire, this Pokémon's flame burns hotter than 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit. It's usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit. When Galar was hit by a harsh cold wave, this Pokémon served as a giant heating stove and saved many lives. While it's engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.

0840.Name: applin
0840.Description: It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by pretending it's just an apple and nothing more. As soon as it's born, it burrows into an apple. Not only does the apple serve as its food source, but the flavor of the fruit determines its evolution.

0841.Name: flapple
0841.Description: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns. Under the influence of Gigantamax energy, it produces much more sweet nectar, and its shape has changed to resemble a giant apple. If it stretches its neck, the strong aroma of its nectar pours out. The scent is so sickeningly sweet that one whiff makes other Pokémon faint. It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.

0842.Name: appletun
0842.Description: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokémon it preys on. It blasts its opponents with massive amounts of sweet, sticky nectar, drowning them under the deluge. Due to Gigantamax energy, this Pokémon's nectar has thickened. The increased viscosity lets the nectar absorb more damage than before. Its body is covered in sweet nectar, and the skin on its back is especially yummy. Children used to have it as a snack.

0843.Name: silicobra
0843.Description: As it digs, it swallows sand and stores it in its neck pouch. The pouch can hold more than 17 pounds of sand. It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.

0844.Name: sandaconda
0844.Description: Its sand pouch has grown to tremendous proportions. More than 1,000,000 tons of sand now swirl around its body. When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened. Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently. Sand swirls around its body with such speed and power that it could pulverize a skyscraper.

0845.Name: cramorant
0845.Description: Cramorant's gluttony led it to try to swallow an Arrokuda whole, which in turn led to Cramorant getting an Arrokuda stuck in its throat. It's so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it's battling midfight. This Cramorant has accidentally gotten a Pikachu lodged in its gullet. Cramorant is choking a little, but it isn't really bothered. The half-swallowed Pikachu is so startled that it isn't struggling yet, but it's still looking for a chance to strike back. The slightest shock is sometimes enough to get this Pokémon to spit out the Arrokuda lodged in its throat. This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokémon other than its preferred prey.

0846.Name: arrokuda
0846.Description: If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It's very proud of that jaw. After it's eaten its fill, its movements become extremely sluggish. That's when Cramorant swallows it up.

0847.Name: barraskewda
0847.Description: This Pokémon has a jaw that's as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda's flesh is surprisingly tasty, too. It spins its tail fins to propel itself, surging forward at speeds of over 100 knots before ramming prey and spearing into them.

0848.Name: toxel
0848.Description: It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokémon, a tingling sensation follows. It manipulates the chemical makeup of its poison to produce electricity. The voltage is weak, but it can cause a tingling paralysis.

0849.Name: toxtricity-amped
0849.Description: Capable of generating 15,000 volts of electricity, this Pokémon looks down on all that would challenge it. Its excessive electric energy is its weapon. This Pokémon can build up more electricity than any thundercloud. When this Pokémon sounds as if it's strumming a guitar, it's actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity. It has an electrical organ on its chest. While generating electricity, it fills its surroundings with what sounds like the strumming of a bass guitar. Out of control after its own poison penetrated its brain, it tears across the land in a rampage, contaminating the earth with toxic sweat. This short-tempered and aggressive Pokémon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.

0850.Name: sizzlipede
0850.Description: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot. It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they're well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.

0851.Name: centiskorch
0851.Description: Gigantamax energy has evoked a rise in its body temperature, now reaching over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. Its heat waves incinerate its enemies. When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies. The heat that comes off a Gigantamax Centiskorch may destabilize air currents. Sometimes it can even cause storms. While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.

0852.Name: clobbopus
0852.Description: It's very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land. Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn't alarmed when that happens—it knows they'll grow back. It's about as smart as a three-year-old.

0853.Name: grapploct
0853.Description: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful. Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.

0854.Name: sinistea
0854.Description: The swirl pattern in this Pokémon's body is its weakness. If it gets stirred, the swirl loses its shape, and Sinistea gets dizzy. This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea. It absorbs the life-force of those who drink it. It waits patiently, but opportunities are fleeting— it tastes so bad that it gets spat out immediately. The teacup in which this Pokémon makes its home is a famous piece of antique tableware. Many forgeries are in circulation.

0855.Name: polteageist
0855.Description: This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found. Trainers Polteageist trusts will be allowed to experience its distinctive flavor and aroma firsthand by sampling just a tiny bit of its tea. Leaving leftover black tea unattended is asking for this Pokémon to come along and pour itself into it, turning the tea into a new Polteageist. When angered, it launches tea from its body at the offender's mouth. The tea causes strong chills if swallowed.

0856.Name: hatenna
0856.Description: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures' emotions. If you don't have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you. If this Pokémon senses a strong emotion, it will run away as fast as it can. It prefers areas without people.

0857.Name: hattrem
0857.Description: No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently. Using the braids on its head, it pummels foes to get them to quiet down. One blow from those braids would knock out a professional boxer.

0858.Name: hatterene
0858.Description: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others. This Pokémon can read the emotions of creatures over 30 miles away. The minute it senses hostility, it goes on the attack. Beams like lightning shoot down from its tentacles. It's known to some as the Raging Goddess. If you're too loud around it, you risk being torn apart by the claws on its tentacle. This Pokémon is also known as the Forest Witch.

0859.Name: impidimp
0859.Description: Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokémon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy. It sneaks into people's homes, stealing things and feasting on the negative energy of the frustrated occupants.

0860.Name: morgrem
0860.Description: When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, it's trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair. With sly cunning, it tries to lure people into the woods. Some believe it to have the power to make crops grow.

0861.Name: grimmsnarl
0861.Description: By transforming its leg hair, this Pokémon delivers power-packed drill kicks that can bore huge holes in Galar's terrain. With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even Machamp. Gigantamax energy has caused more hair to sprout all over its body. With the added strength, it can jump over the world's tallest building. Its hairs work like muscle fibers. When its hairs unfurl, they latch on to opponents, ensnaring them as tentacles would.

0862.Name: obstagoon
0862.Description: Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shout—this move is known as Obstruct. It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.

0863.Name: perrserker
0863.Description: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle. After many battles, it evolved dangerous claws that come together to form daggers when extended.

0864.Name: cursola
0864.Description: Its shell is overflowing with its heightened otherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as protection for this Pokémon's core spirit. Be cautious of the ectoplasmic body surrounding its soul. You'll become stiff as stone if you touch it.

0865.Name: sirfetchd
0865.Description: Only Farfetch'd that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon's leek withers, it will retire from combat. After deflecting attacks with its hard leaf shield, it strikes back with its sharp leek stalk. The leek stalk is both weapon and food.

0866.Name: mr-rime
0866.Description: It's highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements. Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.

0867.Name: runerigus
0867.Description: A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move. Never touch its shadowlike body, or you'll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.

0868.Name: milcery
0868.Description: They say that any patisserie visited by Milcery is guaranteed success and good fortune. This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.

0869.Name: alcremie
0869.Description: Cream pours endlessly from this Pokémon's body. The cream stiffens when compressed by an impact. A harder impact results in harder cream. The moment it evolved, it took on a bitter flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution. The moment it evolved, it took on a complex flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution. The moment it evolved, it took on a mixed flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution. The moment it evolved, it took on a refreshing flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution. The moment it evolved, it took on a salty flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution. The moment it evolved, it took on a sour flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution. The moment it evolved, it took on a sweet and tart flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution. The moment it evolved, it took on an aromatic flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution. When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it's decorated with cream. It launches swarms of missiles, each made of cream and loaded with 100,000 kilocalories. Get hit by one of these, and your head will swim. The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream a bitter flavor. The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream a complex flavor. The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream a mixed flavor. The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream a refreshing flavor. The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream a salty flavor. The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream a sour flavor. The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream a sweet and tart flavor. The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream an aromatic flavor. When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.

0870.Name: falinks
